        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 29 at 7:31AM CDT by NWS Springfield MO</headline>
        <description>At 731 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Mindenmines, or near Pittsburg, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Oakton, Burgess, Liberal, Mindenmines, Irwin, Iantha, Oskaloosa,
Verdella, Lamar Heights, Prairie State Park, Lamar, Hannon, and
Arcadia.

This includes Interstate 49 between mile markers 62 and 76.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 AM CDT for
southeastern Kansas...and southwestern Missouri.</instruction>
